eatment effects were associated with higher relative rates of disease progression. Significant associations between T2 lesion measures and EDSS measures also were found (p {\textless} 0.05), with some suggestion that the strength of the association may differ for older versus newer DMTs.$\backslash$n$\backslash$nCONCLUSIONS: Treatment differences in relapse reduction and T2 lesions are positively related to differences in disease progression over the first two years of treatment.},
